n` that only returns an object through a public method to prevent access.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native image support**\\n\\nI’m questioning if `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError` would compile correctly. It seems that the plugin would allow that, but there’s a potential issue with `CodeSource`, which returns the current executable. If `ModuleFinder.of` throws a `FindException`, that's a runtime exception that might not be caught. Should I only catch `RuntimeException` when it’s native? \\n\\nI can't use a native guard since dynamic loading isn't supported. If this failure manifests as a `FindException`, can I treat it as unsupported according to the rules?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_azO3vzfXiwZo4xWGTeZwyeOL|fc_06458ece8950469c0169faa7f898008190a836943e7944a1c9", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/ByteBuddyAgentTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.ByteBuddyAgent;\nimport reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.Installer;\nimport reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.ByteBuddyAgent.AttachmentProvider;\n", "newText": "import reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.ByteBuddyAgent;\nimport reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.ByteBuddyAgent.AttachmentProvider;\n"}, {"oldText": "import reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.ByteBuddyAgent.AttachmentProvider.Accessor.ExternalAttachment;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n", "newText": "import reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.ByteBuddyAgent.AttachmentProvider.Accessor.ExternalAttachment;\nimport reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.Installer;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n"}, {"oldText": "        public ExternalAttachment getExternalAttachment() {\n            return new ExternalAttachment(Re