[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Java access modifiers**\n\nI’m thinking about how Java's access modifiers work, especially with reflection. When using `Class.getMethod`, it returns public methods, even from package-private classes. Still, invoking those might throw an `IllegalAccessException` if the class isn't public. I remember encountering errors regarding class visibility before. There's also the option of creating a top-level public static nested class if necessary. However, there's a project rule to keep coverage for dynamic-access classes in their specific test files, which makes this tricky.\n\n**Evaluating Java class structure**\n\nI’m thinking about the one-to-one mapping between report classes and generated test class files, and adding a helper Java file might not work well. Perhaps making it a package-private top-level class with a public constructor could be an option? However, there’s a concern about the `javacExecutable` not existing in the JRE, as it typically relies on JAVA_HOME from the JDK. Also, if I'm under a native image, `System.getProperty(\"java.home\")` could point to a directory without javac. But I need to stay focused on the main task.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06458ece8950469c0169faaa69569081909fc563e243c2f8a4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-qp4hfFMIvT1bBOcYDzVIEA3OrFsmJNJu0HQQa5Xzpyp7R6nCvKEH4N8e-ERbesvMTN3PHvO0oI5muAZi4k2u7s0D-fLYPcrwfTURqm4b6NAO7DtmfvZkR3ujuDTIGGimGOd1Vlf8W3DCHllM5dVrmfkoPAZ1qcvrrhuuWIGPR-uO8b8PGQX11bVkRBkdurtnVrgK0fNhV5E3BB7CISAFSwLqNhXGWfLy1WNmOqMHuCVjWD0IQ9q6p9XM5ZRj8pyEp4OzzHpricc9aTi2WcqVAlsj3i7_8yTL07lcW6aYK5I2YQuyydzYDG1IFD0HQp2pIs080xlHcl-PiE7LRAnBpwkLPZ8-9Di_QKIwxy2kcfGqYWwEX-74xRRibBAOG3g88aWrAhHLmtp-xjMFJK2NNZANJ4UzlADr4Gbaska_ZUhlzc56L1EMKpqJgWhsLddhgpTEyujdHHSK5QD-L8XslmJdlvAKUZ5zOdmxKRV3mxSbRqY3SrSqQVPyA3rBFdRmG8_6RTCfJPfFaFyR_u1I_uCSJe1oiHU2-PpKcAPSIHmHGoLNbk-1dQaM31grET33lfgN_4